The public day event at the China Pingju Opera Theater Photo: Courtesy of Huang XinziAs part of the celebrations of the 10th anniversary of the Beijing Performance & Arts Group, the organization has been hosting a series of public events for its troupes.A public event on Saturday for the China Pingju Opera Theater included a forum and talks about the theater's history since 1955 as well as a behind-the-scene look at the making of their well-known original Pingju Opera Rainbow in Tibet.  Hou Hong, president of the China Pingju Opera Theater, announced that a revised version of Rainbow in Tibet will be staged on June 7-8. Fang Tongtong, the director noted that the new version will have some changes to the story. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Delegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los AngelesChinese driving Vegas growthHaving fun